+# Adaptogen Cast Spec (Experimental)
+
+This source-tree mod models the `adaptogen` concept as a language-adjacent runtime bridge.
+The long-term goal is a native PHP cast operator, `(adapt)`, that can consume a class reference
+and execute automation behavior through class-provided static methods.
+
+Headline:
+"Add an Adaptogen cast operator that turns a class reference into a live automation call and inferred value."
+
+Runtime flow expected by the mod:
+1. Accept a class reference target.
+2. Read static `cron()` and `command()` methods from that class.
+3. POST both values to local port `245` using keys `cron` and `command`.
+4. Infer return value type from response body in this fixed order:
+   - integer first, with `0`/`1` coerced to boolean
+   - float
+   - JSON object/array decoded to array-like structure
+   - case-insensitive `true`/`false` strings
+   - plain string fallback
+
+Reasons this can work:
+- The syntax can be concise and memorable, reducing userland glue code.
+- A single local service endpoint can centralize execution policy and cache behavior.
+- Fixed inference order keeps call-site behavior deterministic.
+
+Reasons this can fail:
+- A native cast requires parser/compiler/runtime work and ongoing maintenance.
+- Local HTTP dependency on port `245` can fail operationally.
+- Heuristic inference can misclassify ambiguous outputs without strict conventions.
+
+Implementation note in this tree:
+The accompanying `adaptogen_runtime.py` file provides a Python prototype of the runtime flow so
+behavior can be exercised and tested before any parser-level integration work.
